meanings.definition: To surpass in passing or moving beyond.
meanings.sent1: She outpassed all her classmates in the race.
meanings.sent2: The cheetah outpassed the gazelle in the chase.
meanings.sent3: The tortoise outpassed the hare in the slow and steady race.
meanings.sent4: Her determination outpassed any obstacles in her path.
meanings.sent5: The river outpassed its banks during the heavy rainstorm.

meanings.definition: To exceed in passing or moving beyond.
meanings.sent1: He outpassed his own record in the long jump.
meanings.sent2: The spaceship outpassed the speed of light.
meanings.sent3: The kite outpassed the bird in the sky.
meanings.sent5: The marathon runner outpassed his competitors with ease.
